{"word":"ἀοιδή","slug":"ἀοιδή","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀοιδή</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀείδω'><el>ἀείδω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>song, a singing</i>, whether <i>the art of song</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; or <i>the act of singing, song</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>the thing sung, a song</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>the subject of song</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}